      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PATRIARCH NZ (7) is back today after a layoff of four months. Closed the last preparation in great style with a win by 2.25 metres over 1832m at Albany. Has to contend with a very wide draw. Sure to be ready to run well. AMERICAN FALCON NZ (9) was responsible for a very good effort last time over 2130m at Gloucester Park, finishing second and just a head from the winner. Big chance based on that recent effort. CHUGACH (5) is right in contention after finishing in the placings for the second time in a row last start, beaten a neck into third at Gloucester Park. No reason he cannot take this out. TOBY GEORGE (6) finished 11th last start in a Group One over 2130m at Gloucester Park, beaten 35 metres by Ideal Beach. Top-shelf performer who is nicely placed to return in style.",
